  "dateModified": "2026-04-27",
  "datePublished": "2026-04-27",
  "description": "The rhetorical sequence that anarchist political speech follows regardless of its surface content — a six-step structure that mirror-inverts the corresponding steps of fascist grammar, refusing crisis as urgency, pure community as identity, the enemy as a population, suffering as sacrifice, destiny as inevitability, and inevitability as agency. The framework's analysis is that the inversion does not constitute an exit from the operational closure within which fascist grammar operates; anarchist grammar inhabits the same metabolism as another genre.",
  "name": "Anarchist grammar",
